ess hype?<br>I''m intrigued about this ''viral'' thing. Do people really really see hundreds of banal things on the internet and feel the overwhelming urge to share every one with everybody they know? If they did we''d be bombarded with hundreds or even thousands of ''shares'' every day - I''m not, is anybody else? I think it becomes â€œeveryone else is sharing this/talking about this so I willâ€. Once something hits a certain tipping point it naturally snowballs. I recommend book Adam Kurcharskiâ€™s â€˜ The Rules of Contagion: Why Things Spread - and Why They Stopâ€™ if you are interested in this. Thanks for the recommendation. I''ve just googled the title and it looks like something I''d enjoy. According to this article Tik Tok (which seems to have had a big marketing budget over the last 4 months) is harmless fun. Not a single mention of this <br><a href=""https://www.google.co.uk/amp/s/www.washingtonpost.com/opinions/tiktok-and-the-long-arm-of-the-chinese-government/2019/12/02/1064a72c-1142-11ea-b0fc-62cc38411ebb_story.html%3foutputType=amp"" rel=""nofollow"" data-link-name=""in body link"" class=""u-underline"">https://www.google.co.uk/amp/s/www.washingtonpost.com/opinions/tiktok-and-the-long-arm-of-the-chinese-government/2019/12/02/1064a72c-1142-11ea-b0fc-62cc38411ebb_story.html%3foutputType=amp</a> They fudge the numbers and support. They are able and willing to do this because of where its from. <br>Do your kids a favour and tell them at what cost the silly dance. This is a Chinese app. Be very careful downloading this. What? Should we be equally careful when downloading Facebook, Instagram, Twitter, why? @Maddix123 Would this convince you?<br><a href=""https://www.facebook.com/105488067649967/videos/1477612639081755"" rel=""nofollow"" data-link-name=""in body link"" class=""u-underline"">https://www.facebook.com/105488067649967/videos/1477612639081755</a>/ Great app if you don''t care who is watching your kids. Isn''t that the same for FB, Instgram etc? I''m so worried that the kids are worried. It''s really worrying right now. The ""TikTok poses threat to democracy. And here''s why"" article can''t be far away now. Chinese spyware innit Another app which is diverting minds mainly the young to a useless life of exsistance with no real benefit to society except again making a few wealthy and gathering tons of data on individuals. In a crisis like this a change is needed to focus minds to things that matter, to change the future direction of the world we live in. yeah but it''s really really really harmless fun and it makes me feel good and able to cope with this whole thing. I mean it''s not drugs or alcohol, and I do break up my 6 hour TikTok hole with a brisk walk every now and then What makes you think drugs or alcohol are more harmful than 6 hours of TikTok? Seems like TikTok is mind destroying. Makes a Twitter look like an intellectual paradise in comparison :) Weird, wasnâ€™t TikTok the one we were being warned was an Iranian govt spy platform or something like that? Maybe Iâ€™m too old to understand TikTok, but I found every single video I watched on there terrible to almost mediocre without exception. Im 63 and I do find Tik Tok very addictive a lot of silliness and narcism plenty of eye candy. If your not interested just swipe next. Tik Tok though is very useful to know what people are thinking. Users are very supportive of people with disabilities. The Bullied. People with different views. It has the potential to be a great social movement which frankly has surprised me. you sure. Thank you<a href=""http://www.mapadeespana.es"" rel=""nofollow"" data-link-name=""in body link"" class=""u-underline"">.</a> <a href=""https://www.vox.com/open-sourced/2019/12/16/21013048/tiktok-china-national-security-investigation"" rel=""nofollow"" data-link-name=""in body link"" class=""u-underline"">https://www.vox.com/open-sourced/2019/12/16/21013048/tiktok-china-national-security-investigation</a> thank you! for this comment<a href=""http://www.tik-tok.online"" rel=""nofollow"" data-link-name=""in body link"" class=""u-underline"">.</a> At least it gives nurses something to do. TikTok it''s one of the worst things ever create this century. It''s just a base of stupidities which increases the addiction of the young person to their phones .. I feel so sad when I hear that this app can bring people closer, it''s the exact opposite the people who live in the TikTok world accord more importance to a video of a random guy doing nothing with added value instead to go out with their friends drink a beer and share a real conversation .. It''s like the influencers, do you find that to be normal to have some people paid to just do cramming on you ... I think TikTok is helping a lot of people to face the quarantine due to the coronavirus crisis. It''s good thing, because people can connect to each others, in a funny way. It''s not like instagram or twitter, you don''t have to show a perfect image of yourself on the social media. Like they said on this article, TikTok is only about jokes, weird videos... <br>Thank you for writing an article which it''s describing TikTok in a good way ! Before this crisis, I wasn''t interested in this application. I was only watching videos posted via another social network (like Instagram). I think this app helps people to mentally endure this situation. I find it cool, it allows them to escape. Users can create content and develop their imaginations. They can also be just spectators. Personally, I''m only a spectator and I could spend hours on my phone. It entertains me, makes me laugh. Thanks TikTok. <a class=""js-rec-tooltip-link"" href=""https://profile.theguardian.com/signin?INTCMP=DOTCOM_COMMENTS_SIGNIN_RECOMM"">Sign in</a>
